	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=item.html?item=20790&mid=106018310557076>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=item.html?item=20790&mid=106018310557076>My fun night getting the Book</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=20790&mid=106018310557076#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Aug 6th 11:27 AM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=178657><span id= >Rindred</span></a><br><span id=notbold>59 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.86]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I (finally) attained my Book of Souls on 8/3/03, and here's some things you need to know if you plan to sneak in &quot;solo&quot; to get it.<br><br>First - I know there are player-made maps of the zone; if you don't know how the quickest route to the Maestro's Hall, get a map and draw a line from the zone to there so you know which way to turn. <br><br>Second - Bring a group to clear the bridge at the head of the zone. The mobs on the bridge (four) are random spawns. If they are undead, they'll see through your Hide, and there's no good way to sneak by them short of having someone either pull them, or Calm them. BEFORE you get all hot to go down there, have the Wiz use an &quot;Eye&quot; spell to scout the chamber to make sure the book is actually there. This would have spared me a death when I went in, got spotted, and died running around trying to figure out what went wrong.<br><br>Third - There are two patrollers on the streets along the direct route. For me, it was a Lich and a Revenant, who (of course) both see through Hide. They move along fixed routes, changing positions about every 3 minutes. There are lots of corners and other nooks and crannies for a rogue to hide in while you let the mobs go through their patrol patterns. Be patient. And be careful, the second patroller (closest to the Book) walks right up to a spot right in front of the chamber you want to go in, and you could wind up bumping into him quite by accident.<br><br>Fourth - The building you want is directly across from the steps up to the Maestro's Hall. There's a decorative, free-standing arch right in front of the door to the one you want. The building itself is shaped like a plus sign &quot;+&quot;, with the door being on the &quot;south&quot; end. The book is in the right side chamber of the room, against the right wall, slightly off-center to the north. It's practically a flyspeck-size book. There will be a mob in the dead center of the room, two against the back wall of the &quot;north&quot; chamber, and one against the &quot;north&quot; wall of the right-hand chamber, immediately beside the Book. Just my luck, the mob beside the Book was a Scorn Banshee who - wait for it - sees through Hide. For me, it was the only one who saw through Hide; the other mobs were an Ashebone Drake (middle), Priest of Hate, and an Abhorrent (both on the north wall). If the mob beside the Book engages melee, DON'T try to run away. If you are buffed and can take the abuse for a few seconds, do it; run directly at the Book. The mobs in the other chambers didn't add despite the cramped conditions. They added and killed me the first time because I ran for the door to put my corpse in a more favorable-for-recovery spot.<br><br>Fifth and finally, have an instant escape route planned. If you get spotted, you won't have much time before you're dead. The Banshee was hitting me for as much as 230 damage per swipe, and Bashing like a crazy...well, you get the idea. Call of the Hero would be ideal. Unless the patrollers are aligned in their patterns &quot;just so,&quot; a postponed TL window will probably fade before you can make it there safely. Halfling rogues would be advised to bring the quested version Leatherfoot Raider Skullcap for the Circle of Common insta-port. I decided to wager on my luck, went in with Virtue, Speed of the Shissar, and equipped my Worker Sledgemallet. I got the Book, got taken down to 55% health before I got lined up for my first swing...which proc'ed right away for me.<br><br>Hope these notes prove helpful. Oh, and if you have to drag a corpse back to the zone line for a rez from a failed attempt, use the F9 alternate views to look around corners before charging out. It's as slow as salmon swimming upstream, but necessary to avoid a DOUBLE corpse run.<br><br><br>Rhoth Fairson<br>Lanys T'Vyl<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Aug&nbsp;&nbsp;6 11:21:40 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
